observations.managementAction:
The Municipal Agriculturist commented through her letter dated July 28, 2020 which was noted by the Municipal Mayor that the following actions shall be adopted to improve the project implementation:
• Practice indexing of individual recipients for easy tracking of status and inventory;
• Sustain meeting of carabao raisers organization and provision of assistance such as deworming;
• Send letters to beneficiaries, discuss their obligations as recipients and demand answers as advised;
• Seek the assistance of Barangays in monitoring the project; and
• Coordinate with the Municipal Accountant on deaths of animals and furnish her with copies of report for timely validation.
She also furnished the Audit Team with copies of updated inventory and status reports together with the reports of death of goats, cattle and carabaos.

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Agriculturist to:
complete the conduct of the physical count/inventory of the animals and prepare and render the report thereon;
conduct a complete investigation on the circumstances surrounding the death of the animals and determine the cause/s of death if negligence was committed so that the concerned recipients may be compelled to refund the cost of animals;
identify the recipients of the 10 swine as next beneficiaries and prove with evidence the allegation of the non-receipt of 22 swine by beneficiaries;
render a monitoring report complete with documents to support the beneficiaries of the animal dispersal program who already died, migration/transfer of seven beneficiaries to other places outside the Municipality and the non-existence of two beneficiaries in the Barangay but was alleged as residents of the Barangay.
The Municipal Treasurer must also be required to collect the cost of the swine from its beneficiaries in accordance with the dispersal contract.
